Kreugen you really are missing the point.  Step back from the big raids a second and try to understand this:<br>
<br>
Your comparison is ill formed.  You should be comparing a wizard (or any other casting class) with great loot vs a wizard that has nothing outside of the original release (pre kunark).  Must be quite a difference, right?  Wrong.   They have the same spells available and excluding level differences the same mana pool.  Yes there's tons of nice gear for casters but it doesn't *really* affect their damage output <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   over time</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  Sure a wizard can ks by nuking fast.  So what?  Sustained damage is what counts.  That's how you get exp/axp or beat the raid mobs.  There's a reason you have mostly melee at raids instead of just clerics/wizards/mages/drudis.<br>
<br>
Turn the argument around and try to picture yourself still running around with a sub 1000 ac in valorium armor, a bladestopper, and darkmetal sprinkler.  That's a huge difference in your damage potential and output.   Also imagine no melee or hybrid dmg tunings that have taken place.  That's what casters just got a reprieve from.<br>
<br>
Lastly arguing that not all casters should have access to these items is illogical when vast amounts of kunark and velious weapons and armor are available to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   all</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> melee classes now.  The average sub 50 melee character today is much more powerful than they were before kunark and velious.  THAT is the difference.  Casters have not gotten a proportional increase in effectiveness in that time.  Not even close.<br>
