I think that the tuning that they've done here is fine.  I DON'T think that mages + pets, or wizards, or ANYONE should be able to outdamage rogues over the course of several battles.  Otherwise, most of the niche that Verant has given us is gone.  Things like wizard manaburn...that's FINE!  They SHOULD be able to toast things better than us.  But when you start decreasing mana costs, increasing mana regen capabilities, increasing damage output, and decreasing agro, you come dangerously close to allowing other classes to CONSISTENTLY outdamage rogues.  We can't manaburn, we can't tank as well as the tank classes, we can't cast utility spells, we can't bind, we can't gate.  We can do damage and be stealthy.  I don't think many people will want rogues for groups if we're behind all of the caster classes in damage output OVER TIME, as well as behind in all of those other areas.<br>
